# Rybbit Next.js App Router Integration

## 1. **Placement & Component**
Place the script in your root layout file using Next.js's built-in Script component.

## 2. **Recommended JSX/TSX Snippet**
```jsx
// app/layout.js
import Script from "next/script"

export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <head />
      <body>
        {children}
        <Script
          src="https://app.rybbit.io/api/script.js"
          data-site-id="YOUR_SITE_ID"
          strategy="afterInteractive"
        />
      </body>
    </html>
  )
}
```

## 3. **Strategy**
"`afterInteractive`" is the documented strategy recommendation.

## 4. **Proxy Approach**
Yes, they provide an optional section recommending rewriting through Next.js to bypass ad blockers, noting: "some ad blockers may still agressively block it no matter how the tracking is implemented."

## 5. **next.config.js Rewrites**
```js
async rewrites() {
  return [
    {
      source: "/api/script.js",
      destination: `${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_RYBBIT_HOST}/api/script.js`,
    },
    {
      source: "/api/track",
      destination: `${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_RYBBIT_HOST}/api/track`,
    },
  ]
}
```

## 6. **Script src**
When using the proxy, change to `src="/api/script.js"` instead of the Rybbit domain directly.

## 7. **Client-Side Helper**
Direct `window.rybbit` access with safety checks:
```js
if (typeof window !== 'undefined' && window.rybbit && typeof window.rybbit.event === 'function') {
  window.rybbit.event('button_click', { buttonTitle: title });
}
```

## 8. **TypeScript Declarations**
```ts
declare global {
  interface Window {
    rybbit?: {
      event: (eventName: string, eventData?: Record<string, any>) => void;
      pageview: () => void;
    };
  }
}
```

